From this project, I realized how important it is to have a GitHub project setup, even if you're a solo developer working on a project. I knew very little about GitHub beforehand, due to having some assignments on it in the past. However, I only ever learnt the basics of GitHub such as how to post your code online, how to access other users codes and projects, and how to assign yourself to a task. However, I never knew what a pull request was, nor what a .mb file is. However, starting this project, I learnt a lot aboout GitHub and will now be using it for future projects and assignments. I realized how useful it is to store your code online in this website, publicly or privately. I've worked on quiet a few projects before and I realized how messy it got storing all of them. I ended up deleting some of them too as it got too messy. However, now that I know how to use GitHub, I will be starting to use it more often.

It was quiet challenging learning GitHub since at first I wasn't really interested in learning it, as I thought it was quiet pointless. However, know that I had to learn it for this assignment, I realized how important it is and now realize why a lot of others use it aswell. The most challenging part for me, was learning the different terms used in GitHub such as pull request and issues. At first I thought issues meant bugs that needed to be fixed within the program, but now the basic idea behind it is that it's tasks everyone working on the project can access.
If I had more time, I would start looking into how I could manage projects with other people. I would also look more into how to manage pull requests, as it was also one of the most things that was challenging to me.
For future improvements, I should do more research on how to use GitHub, especially pull requests and merging.
